<br>
<br>
<br>
1. Clerics and Paladins don't pay. They get enough grief from rez beggars, and don't need to put up with some wizard or druid haggling over price. Besides, never know when you might need a cleric or paladin friend.<br>
<br>
2a. Don't expect me to port halfway around the world just to pick you up. If you expect me to drop what I'm doing and come pick you up, expect to offer at least 300pp, preferably more. This is the only exception to rule 1.<br>
<br>
2b. Don't get angry at me when I tell you to take the Nexus from Dreadlands to GFay instead of me porting there to TL you.<br>
<br>
3. Don't begin your port request with a tell that contains only the words &quot;Hello.&quot; or &quot;Hey friend!&quot;. We know damned well what you want, and don't have time to sit around while you waffle for half an hour before getting to the fucking point.<br>
<br>
4. If you want a translocate from a wizard, know which ports need fragments. Specifically, if it isn't bind or a big spire, it needs a frag. These fragments are not free, and offering 1 or more for your translocate will earn you a much warmer response from the wizard in question. (I've been known to put groups on hold to translocate people that offer fragments.) These fragments sell for 1pp1gp at Temple of Solusek Ro, and have zero weight, so don't worry about them weighing you down, monk. It's a good idea for you to carry a stack at all times.<br>
<br>
5a. If you offer pp for a port in auction, don't withdraw the offer of pp when you find out it's a translocate. This is a sure way to guarantee that you're going to be walking, or worse. I left a 22 warrior in Cazic Thule last week when he did that.<br>
<br>
5b. Don't &quot;forget&quot; that translocates mean the wizard doesn't follow you. If you want a translocate, and offer to pay for it, give the wizard in question the money before you start asking if they're going to start casting.<br>
<br>
6. Know what translocates actually exist. There is no such thing as a translocate to South Ro, nor is there a translocate to Emerald Jungle or Skyfire Mountains. And if you ask me to translocate you to a plane, expect me to swat you upside the head repeatedly and painfully.<br>
<br>
<br>
Follow those rules, and we'll all be much happier. You might even find that wizards in good moods cancel trade windows instead of accepting your money. I know I usually do, and am more likely to do so for people when they're nice and polite about it. <p><center><embed src="http://rkroll.magma.ca/aurie/aurianne.swf" quality=high bgcolor=#FFFFFF width=430 height=65 wmode=window 

